Johannesburg - A festive mood has gripped Vilakazi Street in Orlando West as jovial ANC members and the party's top leadership gathered along the famous street for a mini-rally aimed at mobilising support for the party's 105th birthday bash on Sunday. By midday restaurants in the area such as Sakhumzi and Vuyo's were packed while some streets were cordoned off. Young and old marshals, including grannies, were deployed to control the crowd.&nbsp;ANC secretary-general Gwede Mantashe arrived a little after lunchtime and waved to members.Before his arrival, Sports and Recreation Minister Fikile Mbalula brought along his bubbly character and interacted with the crowd, taking selfies with supporters. He was joined by ANC treasurer-general Zweli Mkhize. President Jacob Zuma is also expected to grace the rally. #ANCSG @GwedeMantashe1 joined by @MbalulaFikile on Vilakazi street in Soweto. #ANCFriday #UnityInAction #ANC105 pic.twitter.com/LDpCM7LsiO#ANCSG @GwedeMantashe1 joined by @MbalulaFikile on Vilakazi street in Soweto. #ANCFriday #UnityInAction #ANC105 pic.twitter.com/LDpCM7LsiO MyANC (@MYANC) January 6, 2017</blockquote> #ANCVilakazi #UnityInAction Towards #ANC105 #WeAreANC pic.twitter.com/ND6YvRojZS#ANCVilakazi #UnityInAction Towards #ANC105 #WeAreANC pic.twitter.com/ND6YvRojZS MyANC (@MYANC) January 6, 2017</blockquote> #ANCTGMkhize has arrived at Vilakazi Street in Soweto pic.twitter.com/icVxJ4odJm#ANCTGMkhize has arrived at Vilakazi Street in Soweto pic.twitter.com/icVxJ4odJm MyANC (@MYANC) January 6, 2017</blockquote> Meanwhile, the street is a sea of black, green and gold. High fashion has also been doing the rounds. Women are dressed in their regalia which includes dresses and headwraps. A mobile stage has been set up with plenty of entertainment expected throughout the day.More people are expected to gather on the street which boasts the Nelson Mandela Museum. Bishop Desmond Tutu's house is also located on Vilakazi Street.The Star